When setting up the Raspberry Pi:
clone the repository to the Desktop folder

run the command:
sudo nano /etc/rc.local

and then paste:
cd SeniorDesign
pip3 install -r requirements.txt

to the end of the file to enable automatic pulling of the code base

Next, create a file called LOCAL_CONSTANTS.py in RaspberryPiController folder. Copy over the contents of LOCAL_CONSTANTS_SAMPLE.py and
modify the appropriate constants.

To launch the vehicle, from the RaspberryPiController folder run:
python3 vehicle.py

IF YOU DOWNLOAD A LIBRARY PLEASE ADD IT TO requirements.txt
